Content:: Russian sanctions against Ukraine were put into effect by the November 1, 2018, Order of the Government of Russia No. 1300 [1] in pursuance of the October 22, 2018 Decree of the President of Russia No. 592.[2] The decree imposed economic sanctions on 322 Ukrainian citizens and 68 Ukrainian companies. The sanctions affect only the assets of the listed persons and companies within the territory of Russia.[3] This article related to politics in Russia is a stub.
